# Toronto Rising — multiplayer authority (pre–second-client)

**Execution model:** TTS runs **all mod Lua on the host only**. Connected clients do not run the Global script or object scripts. Clients transmit interactions; host Lua executes once; the engine replicates world/object state.

**Until TOR-144 (multiplayer E2E) passes with two real clients**, treat solo Host Save & Play as **insufficient** proof for join-client behavior (P10 live `gameState` broadcast gap, per-client UI visibility, replication timing).

Canonical policies **P1–P10**, pre-flight checklist, and first-session script: [`.dev/Multiplayer Functionality/Preparing For Multiplayer.md`](../../.dev/Multiplayer%20Functionality/Preparing%20For%20Multiplayer.md) §1.

Verification playbook: [`.dev/E2E Playbooks/Multiplayer-E2E.md`](../../.dev/E2E%20Playbooks/Multiplayer-E2E.md).

**Rule of thumb:** *One Lua brain (the host). Stop asking "which machine am I." Only ask "which player did this?" and "who should see this UI?"*

## Mandatory on every feature touching players, objects, load, or world I/O

1. **Classify delivery:** host-executed event (`onLoad`, `onObjectDrop`, `Global.call`, …) vs clicker-only (`HUD_*`, object `click_*`).
2. **Classify tier:** A UI / B state / C world — [Preparing For Multiplayer](../../.dev/Multiplayer%20Functionality/Preparing%20For%20Multiplayer.md).
3. **Tier C runs on host** because TTS runs mod Lua on the host only — do not skip reconciler work behind dead execution gates.
4. **Actor identity:** ST-only interaction → `U.isStorytellerSteamPlayer(playerRef)` on the event's player param.
5. **Object-script mutations → `Global.call`** to Global entries (bundle-safe); Global may steam-gate ST-only actions. **`GlobalIsStorytellerSteamPlayer` only** from object scripts.
6. **O(1) tag/GUID guard** before heavy work in hot handlers (TOR-197).
7. **No dual apply** — one physical channel per intent; fingerprint or invalidate when needed.
8. **Object scripts:** no `require("core.*")` for mutations — pattern: `objects/npc_control_board.ttslua`, `objects/dice_bag.ttslua`.
9. **New handlers:** add a row to [Event Listener Policy](../../.dev/Sychronizing%20Game%20Functionality/Event%20Listener%20Policy.md) (delivery + tier).
10. **P10 live `gameState` broadcast gap** — fix via sync bridge, not execution gates.

## Agent completion checklist (Lua / sync changes)

Before marking work done:

- [ ] ST-only paths use `isStorytellerSteamPlayer` on the event's player param; per-client UI uses XmlUI `visibility`.
- [ ] Hot paths: O(1) tag/GUID guard before `require` / `Sync.*` (TOR-197).
- [ ] Mutation → narrow `Sync.*`; no dual apply without fingerprint ([Dual-apply survey](../../.dev/Sychronizing%20Game%20Functionality/Dual_apply_survey.md)).
- [ ] Object scripts route mutations via `Global.call`; no `require("core.*")`.
- [ ] Event Listener Policy inventory updated if handlers added/changed.
- [ ] Solo smoke if touching gameboard or rolls (Apply/Clear, one roll path); hotseat smoke if execution-model related; note **multiclient unverified** in Linear comment unless TOR-144 exercised.

## High-risk surfaces (grep when touching)

Load/bootstrap, gameboard Apply/Clear, token drop/pick-up, scenes/soundscape HUD, dice/rolls, signal candle, character sheet mutators, player connect/seat (**TOR-345** auto-assign), phase Advance/connect blindfold (**TOR-143** / **TOR-319**) — see Preparing §1.3.

## Linear

Multiplayer sync work is **not Done** until **TOR-144 (multiplayer E2E)** passes. Comment on related issues when adding event handlers or Global mutators.
